Nuclear cardiology and echocardiography for the assessment of myocardial viability. The review aims to make a comparative analysis of the nuclear cardiology and echocardiographic approaches for the assessment of myocardial viability on the basis of the most recent literature. Preliminarily the most extensively used methods are described: 1) metabolic tracers, especially as regards FDG-F18 (quantitative uptake mismatch FDG uptake/perfusion)